tux-im (0.1.0-5) resolute; urgency=medium

  * fix(main): Ctrl+C now actually quits the engine.  The old code
    registered Python signal.signal(SIGINT) handlers that called
    IBus.quit() — but IBus.main() runs a GLib MainLoop which
    intercepts UNIX signals itself, so the Python handlers were
    never invoked and the engine hung on Ctrl+C.  Now uses
    GLibUnix.signal_add (with a fallback to the deprecated
    GLib.unix_signal_add) which registers a callback that runs
    INSIDE the main loop when the signal arrives.  signal.signal()
    is kept as a fallback for the pre-loop startup window.

 -- TUX IM contributors <tux-im@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 10:59:00 +0000

tux-im (0.1.0-4) resolute; urgency=medium

  * fix(wbpy): actually feed keys to BOTH wubi and google pinyin
    engines in parallel.  The old code did a serial fallback (try
    wubi first; if it handled the key, return without ever asking
    pinyin) so most pinyin candidates were never shown.  Now every
    letter is fed to both engines; tone digits (1-5) go to pinyin
    only and do not advance the wubi buffer, so wubi decoding stays
    correct across pinyin-with-tone inputs.  Visible buffer mirrors
    the pinyin engine's buffer (the authoritative representation
    including any tone digit).  Adds 4 regression tests in
    tests/test_wbpy.py.

 -- TUX IM contributors <tux-im@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 10:50:00 +0000

tux-im (0.1.0-3) resolute; urgency=medium

  * fix(config): _merge must handle PEP 563 forward-ref annotations and
    generic container inner types.  After 0.1.0-2 the engine still
    crashed on startup because `from __future__ import annotations`
    turns every annotation into a string, so `fields[k].type` was the
    string "str" / "list[str]" and isinstance() rejected it.  Now uses
    typing.get_type_hints() to resolve annotations to real types, and
    checks container inner types (list[T].__args__[0]) explicitly.
    Adds tests/test_config.py with regression coverage.

 -- TUX IM contributors <tux-im@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 10:42:00 +0000

tux-im (0.1.0-2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * fix(config): _merge must read field TYPES, not values.  Use
    __dataclass_fields__[k].type instead of asdict() so the runtime
    type check in Config._apply does not crash on startup with
    "TypeError: isinstance() arg 2 must be a type, ...".

 -- TUX IM contributors <tux-im@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 10:36:00 +0000

